notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Start Backup Process
components.description: Initial placeholder task that starts the backup workflow.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; root of the DAG.

components.name: Determine Backup Strategy
components.description: Evaluates the execution date to decide whether to run a full backup (Saturday) or an incremental backup (weekdays).

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the start task completes successfully.

components.name: Full Backup
components.description: Performs a simulated full database backup; executed only on Saturdays.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when the splitter routes to the full backup branch (Saturday).

components.name: Incremental Backup
components.description: Performs a simulated incremental backup of changed data; executed on weekdays.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when the splitter routes to the incremental backup branch (weekday).

components.name: Verify Backup
components.description: Validates backup integrity and completeness after either full or incremental backup; runs when at least one backup branch succeeds.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after at least one backup task succeeds and none have failed (trigger_rule='none_failed_min_one_success').

components.name: Backup Complete
components.description: Final placeholder task that marks the backup workflow as completed.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful verification of the backup.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: Scheduled DAG trigger (daily run at @daily) providing execution date context
intermediate_datasets: Simulated full backup artifact (produced by full_backup task)
Simulated incremental backup artifact (produced by incremental_backup task)
